== Overview ==
The Saeki clan traces its origins to {{ill|Amenootsuhiko|ja|еӨ©жҠјж—Ҙе‘Ҫ}} (Ame no Oshi-hi no Mikoto), who guided {{ill|Ninigi|ja|еҪҰзҒ«з“ҠгҖ…жқөе°Ҡ}} during the {{ill|Descent of the heavenly grandson|ja|еӨ©еӯ«йҷҚиҮЁ}}. The clan split from the {{ill|ЕҢtomo clan|ja|еӨ§дјҙж°Ҹ}} under the leadership of {{ill|ЕҢtomo no Muroya|ja|еӨ§дјҙе®ӨеұӢ}}, becoming a {{ill|Shinbetsu|ja|зҘһеҲҘ}} (descendant of deities) lineage of {{ill|Tenshin|ja|еӨ©жҙҘзҘһ}} origin. The clan name "Saeki" is believed to derive from their role in guarding the imperial court, as they were seen as those who "block (йҒ® sahe) external threats." This evolved into "Saeki" (гҒ•гҒҲгҒҚ) in modern phonetics, and in some cases as "Saiki" (гҒ•гӮҗгҒҚ).

