The Saeki name was carried on by families like the Ono family, who produced the herbalist {{ill|Ono Ranzan|ja|е°ҸйҮҺиҳӯеұұ|qq=draft}}, and artists such as {{ill|Kishi Ganku|ja|еІёй§’|qq=draft}} of the Kishi school.

