'''Saeki Clan''' (дҪҗдјҜж°Ҹ) is a {{ill|Clan|de|Clan|ja|ж°Ҹ|1=Uji (clan)|lt=Uji|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Clan|13=User:Immanuelle/Uji (clan)|qq=}} whose name is "Saeki".

__TOC__{{-}}

== Overview ==
During the time of {{ill|Descent of the Heavenly Grandson|de|Abstieg des Himmelsnachkommen|ja|еӨ©еӯ«йҷҚиҮЁ|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Descent of the Heavenly Grandson|qq=}}, the ancestor, {{ill|Ninigi|de|Ninigi|ja|гғӢгғӢгӮ®|lt=Hikohirakininomikoto|lt_ja=еҪҰзҒ«з“ҠгҖ…жқөе°Ҡ|lt_de=Hikohirakininomikoto|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ninigi|qq=}}, who was led by {{ill|Amenooshihi|de|Amenooshihi|ja|гӮўгғЎгғҺгӮӘгӮ·гғ’|lt=Heavenly Push Day Deity|lt_ja=еӨ©жҠјж—Ҙе‘Ҫ|lt_de=Amenooshihi|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Amenooshihi|qq=}}, (Amenooshihi no Mikoto), is said to be the progenitor, and it is a {{ill|Divine Separation|de|Divine Separation|ja|зҘһеҲҘ|1=Shinbetsu|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Divine Separation|13=User:Immanuelle/Shinbetsu|qq=}} clan that split from the Otomo clan during the time of {{ill|Otomo no Sukune|de|Otomo no Sukune|ja|еӨ§дјҙе®ӨеұӢ|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Otomo no Sukune|qq=}} {{sfn|ж—Ҙжң¬еӨ§зҷҫз§‘е…Ёжӣё}}<ref>вҖҳ{{ill|New Compilation of Surnames|de|Neue Zusammenstellung der Familiennamen|ja|ж–°ж’°е§“ж°ҸйҢІ|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/New Compilation of Surnames|qq=}}вҖҷ {{ill|Sakyo|de|Sakyo|ja|е·Ұдә¬|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sakyo|qq=}}, in the Divine Separation section.</ref>. After serving the royal authority and undertaking duties such as palace security, there is a theory that they came to be called "Saeki", a term meaning "those who block" (йҒ®гҒҺгӮӢиҖ…), referring to repelling external enemy attacks ({{ill|Historical Kana Usage|de|Historische Kana-Nutzung|ja|жӯҙеҸІзҡ„д»®еҗҚйҒЈ|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Historical Kana Usage|qq=}} spells it "saheki", while {{ill|Modern Kana Usage|de|Moderne Kana-Nutzung|ja|зҸҫд»Јд»®еҗҚйҒЈгҒ„|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Modern Kana Usage|qq=}} spells it "saeki"). There is also a dialectal pronunciation "saiki" (also "sawiki").

As the central {{ill|BanzЕҚ|de|BanzЕҚ|ja|дјҙйҖ |qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/BanzЕҚ|qq=}}, they led the {{ill|Saeki Faction|de|Saeki-Abteilung|ja|дҪҗдјҜйғЁ|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Saeki Faction|qq=}}, serving the {{ill|Imperial Court|de|Kaiserhof|ja|жңқе»· (ж—Ҙжң¬)|lt=Imperial Court|lt_ja=жңқе»·|lt_de=Kaiserhof|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Imperial Court|qq=}} as palace gate guards and as a military force. Incidentally, the palace gate in charge of security was named {{ill|Saeki Gate|de|Saeki-Tor|ja|дҪҗдјҜй–Җ|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Saeki Gate|qq=}} after the clan name, but at the {{ill|Heian Palace|de|Heian-Palast|ja|е№іе®үе®®|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Heian Palace|qq=}}, under the influence of {{ill|Tang-style Culture|de|Tang-Kultur|ja|е”җйўЁж–ҮеҢ–|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tang-style Culture|qq=}}, it was renamed to {{ill|Moss Wall Gate|de|Mooswandtor|ja|и—»еЈҒй–Җ|lt=Moss Wall Gate (SЕҚheki Gate)|lt_ja=и—»еЈҒпјҲгҒқгҒҶгҒёгҒҚпјүй–Җ|lt_de=Mooswandtor|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Moss Wall Gate|qq=}}<ref>вҖҳ{{ill|Nihon Kiriyaku|de|Nihon Kiriyaku|ja|ж—Ҙжң¬зҙҖз•Ҙ|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nihon Kiriyaku|qq=}}вҖҷ {{ill|KЕҚnin|de|KЕҚnin|ja|ејҳд»Ғ|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/KЕҚnin|qq=}} 9th year ({{ill|818 AD|de|818|ja|818е№ҙ|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/818 AD|qq=}}) April 27 clause.</ref>. The {{ill|Kabane|de|Kabane|ja|гӮ«гғҗгғҚ|lt=Surname|lt_ja=е§“|lt_de=Nachname|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kabane|qq=}} was originally {{ill|Ren|de|Ren|ja|йҖЈ|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ren|qq=}}, but in the 13th year of {{ill|Emperor Tenmu|de|Kaiser Tenmu|ja|еӨ©жӯҰеӨ©зҡҮ|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Emperor Tenmu|qq=}} ({{ill|685 AD|de|685|ja|685е№ҙ|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/685 AD|qq=}}), together with members of the same group such as the {{ill|Otomo Clan|de|Otomo-Clan|ja|еӨ§дјҙж°Ҹ|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Otomo Clan|qq=}}, they were granted the surname {{ill|Sukunabe|de|Sukunabe|ja|е®ҝзҰ°|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sukunabe|qq=}}. In the {{ill|Main Palace Office|de|Hauptpalastamt|ja|дё»ж®ҝеҜ®|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Main Palace Office|qq=}}, the name of the Saeki faction remains as one of the noble divisions.

Notable figures include {{ill|Saeki Komaro|de|Saeki Komaro|ja|дҪҗдјҜеӯҗйә»е‘Ӯ|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Saeki Komaro|qq=}}, who, following {{ill|Prince Nakano-ЕҢe|de|Prinz Nakano-ЕҢe|ja|дёӯеӨ§е…„зҡҮеӯҗ|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Prince Nakano-ЕҢe|qq=}}, assassinated {{ill|Soga no Iruka|de|Soga no Iruka|ja|иҳҮжҲ‘е…Ҙй№ҝ|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Soga no Iruka|qq=}}, and {{ill|Saeki Imao Hito|de|Saeki Imao Hito|ja|дҪҗдјҜд»ҠжҜӣдәә|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Saeki Imao Hito|qq=}}, who was active in government from the Nara to the Heian period and held positions such as {{ill|Councillor|de|Berater|ja|еҸӮиӯ°|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Councillor|qq=}} and {{ill|Dazai no Mikoto|de|Dazai no Mikoto|ja|еӨӘе®°еёҘ|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Dazai no Mikoto|qq=}}. The clan also produced many warriors, including {{ill|Saeki Tankeide|de|Saeki Tankeide|ja|дҪҗдјҜдё№зөҢжүӢ|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Saeki Tankeide|qq=}} (the father of Komaro), who, following {{ill|Soga no Umako|de|Soga no Umako|ja|иҳҮжҲ‘йҰ¬еӯҗ|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Soga no Umako|qq=}}, executed {{ill|Prince Anahobe|de|Prinz Anahobe|ja|з©ҙз©ӮйғЁзҡҮеӯҗ|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Prince Anahobe|qq=}}; {{ill|Saeki Ishiyu|de|Saeki Ishiyu|ja|дҪҗдјҜзҹіж№Ҝ|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Saeki Ishiyu|qq=}}, the Ezo General after the conquest of Echigo; and {{ill|Saeki Katsuragi|de|Saeki Katsuragi|ja|дҪҗдјҜи‘ӣеҹҺ|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Saeki Katsuragi|qq=}} (the grandson of Ishiyu), the Deputy General of the Eastern Expedition.

Apart from Imao Hito, no one ascended to the position of {{ill|Giseikan|de|Giseikan|ja|иӯ°ж”ҝе®ҳ|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Giseikan|qq=}} {{sfn|ж—Ҙжң¬еӨ§зҷҫз§‘е…Ёжӣё}}, and the clan eventually declined from being mid-level nobles to lower-Ranked officials ({{ill|Underground Officials|de|Underground Officials|ja|ең°дёӢе®¶|1=Jigeke|2=ja|3=ең°дёӢе®¶|lt=Jigeke|lt=Underground Officials|lt_ja=ең°дёӢе®ҳдәә|lt_de=Underground Officials|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Underground Officials|13=User:Immanuelle/Jigeke|qq=}}). Until around the {{ill|Sengoku Period|de|Sengoku-Zeit|ja|жҲҰеӣҪжҷӮд»Ј (ж—Ҙжң¬)|lt=Sengoku Period|lt_ja=жҲҰеӣҪжҷӮд»Ј|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sengoku Period|qq=}}, together with the {{ill|Otomo Clan|de|Otomo-Clan|ja|еӨ§дјҙж°Ҹ|lt=Otomo Clan|lt_ja=дјҙж°Ҹ|lt_de=Otomo Clan|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Otomo Clan|qq=}}, {{ill|Wake Clan|de|Wake Clan|ja|е’Ңж°—ж°Ҹ|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Wake Clan|qq=}}, and the {{ill|Baekje Royal Family|de|Baekje-KГ¶nigsfamilie|ja|зҷҫжёҲзҺӢж°Ҹ|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Baekje Royal Family|qq=}}, the clan was considered one that received {{ill|Noble Titles|de|Adelstitel|ja|ж°ҸзҲө|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Noble Titles|qq=}} upon the accession of an emperor<ref>{{ill|Tajima no Kimoto|de|Tajima no Kimoto|ja|з”°еі¶е…¬|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tajima no Kimoto|qq=}} "The Establishment of Noble Titles вҖ“ Rituals, Service, and Conferment" in {{sfn|еҸІжһ—}} 71-1, {{ill|1988 AD|de|1988|ja|1988е№ҙ|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1988 AD|qq=}}, p. 61</ref>.

Among the lower-Ranked officials bearing the Saeki name, there is the {{ill|Ono Family|de|Ono-Familie|ja|е°ҸйҮҺе®¶ (дҪҗдјҜе§“)|lt=Ono Family|lt_ja=е°ҸйҮҺе®¶|lt_de=Ono-Familie|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ono Family|qq=}}, which produced the materia medica scholar {{ill|Ono Ransan|de|Ono Ransan|ja|е°ҸйҮҺиҳӯеұұ|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ono Ransan|qq=}}, and the painter {{ill|Kishi Koma|de|Kishi Koma|ja|еІёй§’|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kishi Koma|qq=}}, who founded the {{ill|Kishi School|de|Kishi-Schule|ja|еІёжҙҫ|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kishi School|qq=}} and served the {{ill|Arisugawa-no-miya|de|Arisugawa-no-miya|ja|жңүж –е·қе®®|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Arisugawa-no-miya|qq=}} family, bearing the Saeki name.

== Related Clans ==
=== Saeki Tsukuri ===
'''Saeki Tsukuri''' (-Miyatsuko) appears in the вҖҳ{{ill|New Compilation of Surnames|de|Neue Zusammenstellung der Familiennamen|ja|ж–°ж’°е§“ж°ҸйҢІ|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/New Compilation of Surnames|qq=}}вҖҷ under the {{ill|Right Capital|de|Rechte Hauptstadt|ja|еҸідә¬|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Right Capital|qq=}} Divine Separation section, and his former name was "Saeki Faction". According to the {{ill|Nihon Shoki|de|Nihon Shoki|ja|ж—Ҙжң¬жӣёзҙҖ|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nihon Shoki|qq=}}, he was a retainer of {{ill|Prince Ichinobe Oshi|de|Prinz Ichinobe Oshi|ja|еёӮиҫәжҠјзЈҗзҡҮеӯҗ|lt=Ichinobe Oshi|lt_ja=гҒ„гҒЎгҒ®гҒёгҒ®гҒҠгҒ—гҒҜгҒ®гҒҝгҒ“|lt_de=Ichinobe Oshi|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Prince Ichinobe Oshi|qq=}} and a descendant of {{ill|Saeki Faction Naka-chiko|de|Saeki Fraktion Naka-chiko|ja|дҪҗдјҜйғЁд»Іеӯҗ|lt=Naka-chiko|lt_ja=гҒӘгҒӢгҒЎгҒ“|lt_de=Naka-chiko|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Saeki Faction Naka-chiko|qq=}}<ref>In the Pre-accession Annals of {{ill|Emperor YЕ«ryaku|de|Kaiser YЕ«ryaku|ja|йӣ„з•ҘеӨ©зҡҮ|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Emperor YЕ«ryaku|qq=}}, in the 3rd year, October 1 clause of {{ill|Emperor Ankan|de|Kaiser Ankan|ja|е®үеә·еӨ©зҡҮ|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Emperor Ankan|qq=}}, he is referred to as "Saeki Faction Uruba" (вҖ“uruba), also known as "Naka-teko" (гҒӘгҒӢгҒЎгҒ“).</ref> and, in the 5th year, February 5 clause of {{ill|Emperor Ninken|de|Kaiser Ninken|ja|д»ҒиіўеӨ©зҡҮ|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Emperor Ninken|qq=}}, he was appointed to oversee the Saeki factions from various provinces.

=== Saeki Obito ===
'''Saeki Obito''' (-Obito) appears in the вҖҳ{{ill|New Compilation of Surnames|de|Neue Zusammenstellung der Familiennamen|ja|ж–°ж’°е§“ж°ҸйҢІ|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/New Compilation of Surnames|qq=}}вҖҷ in {{ill|Kawachi Province|de|Kawachi-Provinz|ja|жІіеҶ…еӣҪ|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kawachi Province|qq=}} under the {{ill|Divine Separation|de|Divine Separation|ja|зҘһеҲҘ|1=Shinbetsu|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Divine Separation|13=User:Immanuelle/Shinbetsu|qq=}} category.

== Saeki Faction ==
The Saeki Clan oversaw the central {{ill|Saeki Faction|de|Saeki-Abteilung|ja|дҪҗдјҜйғЁ|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Saeki Faction|qq=}} within the {{ill|Official Division|de|Amtliche Abteilung|ja|е“ҒйғЁ|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Official Division|qq=}},<ref>{{Cite kotobank|Saeki Clan|encyclopedia=Sekai Dai Hyakka Jiten 2nd edition|accessdate=2021-12-19}}</ref> while the regional Saeki Faction was overseen by {{ill|Saeki Nao|de|Saeki Nao|ja|дҪҗдјҜзӣҙ|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Saeki Nao|qq=}} {{sfn|ж—Ҙжң¬еӨ§зҷҫз§‘е…Ёжӣё}}.

