'''Saeki Clan''' (дҪҗдјҜж°Ҹ) is a [[:en:Uji (clan)|Uji]] whose name is "Saeki".

__TOC__{{-}}

== Overview ==
During the time of [[:en:Tenson kЕҚrin|Descent of the Heavenly Grandson]], the ancestor, [[:en:Ninigi-no-Mikoto|Hikohirakininomikoto]], who was led by {{ill|Amenooshihi|de|Amenooshihi|ja|гӮўгғЎгғҺгӮӘгӮ·гғ’|lt=Heavenly Push Day Deity|lt_ja=еӨ©жҠјж—Ҙе‘Ҫ|lt_de=Amenooshihi|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Amenooshihi|qq=|1=AmanЕҚshihi|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q10939616}}, (Amenooshihi no Mikoto), is said to be the progenitor, and it is a {{ill|Divine Separation|de|Divine Separation|ja|зҘһеҲҘ|1=Shinbetsu|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Divine Separation|13=User:Immanuelle/Shinbetsu|qq=}} clan that split from the Otomo clan during the time of {{ill|Otomo no Sukune|de|Otomo no Sukune|ja|еӨ§дјҙе®ӨеұӢ|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Otomo no Sukune|qq=|1=Muroya Ootomo|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11432336}} {{sfn|ж—Ҙжң¬еӨ§зҷҫз§‘е…Ёжӣё}}<ref>вҖҳ[[:en:Shinsen ShЕҚjiroku|New Compilation of Surnames]]вҖҷ [[:en:Sakyo|Sakyo]], in the Divine Separation section.</ref>. After serving the royal authority and undertaking duties such as palace security, there is a theory that they came to be called "Saeki", a term meaning "those who block" (йҒ®гҒҺгӮӢиҖ…), referring to repelling external enemy attacks ([[:en:Historical kana orthography|Historical Kana Usage]] spells it "saheki", while [[:en:Modern kana usage|Modern Kana Usage]] spells it "saeki"). There is also a dialectal pronunciation "saiki" (also "sawiki").

As the central {{ill|BanzЕҚ|de|BanzЕҚ|ja|дјҙйҖ |qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/BanzЕҚ|qq=|comment=changed title based on wikidata|1=Tomomiyatsuko|WD=Q11381545}}, they led the [[:en:Saeki people|Saeki Faction]], serving the {{ill|Imperial Court|de|Kaiserhof|ja|жңқе»· (ж—Ҙжң¬)|lt=Imperial Court|lt_ja=жңқе»·|lt_de=Kaiserhof|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Imperial Court|qq=|comment=changed title based on wikidata|1=Imperial Court of Japan|WD=Q30253177}} as palace gate guards and as a military force. Incidentally, the palace gate in charge of security was named {{ill|Saeki Gate|de|Saeki-Tor|ja|дҪҗдјҜй–Җ|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Saeki Gate|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to и—»еЈҒй–Җ|1=SЕҚhekimon|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q17995614}} after the clan name, but at the [[:en:Heian Palace|Heian Palace]], under the influence of {{ill|Tang-style Culture|de|Tang-Kultur|ja|е”җйўЁж–ҮеҢ–|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tang-style Culture|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to еӨ©е№іж–ҮеҢ–|1=TenpyЕҚ culture|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q5525117}}, it was renamed to {{ill|Moss Wall Gate|de|Mooswandtor|ja|и—»еЈҒй–Җ|lt=Moss Wall Gate (SЕҚheki Gate)|lt_ja=и—»еЈҒпјҲгҒқгҒҶгҒёгҒҚпјүй–Җ|lt_de=Mooswandtor|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Moss Wall Gate|qq=|1=SЕҚhekimon|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q17995614}}<ref>вҖҳ[[:en:Nihon Kiryaku|Nihon Kiriyaku]]вҖҷ [[:en:KЕҚnin (era)|KЕҚnin]] 9th year ([[:en:818|818 AD]]) April 27 clause.</ref>. The [[:en:Kabane|Surname]] was originally [[:en:Muraji|Ren]], but in the 13th year of [[:en:Emperor Tenmu|Emperor Tenmu]] ([[:en:685|685 AD]]), together with members of the same group such as the [[:en:ЕҢtomo clan (ancient)|Otomo Clan]], they were granted the surname [[:en:Sukune|Sukunabe]]. In the {{ill|Main Palace Office|de|Hauptpalastamt|ja|дё»ж®ҝеҜ®|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Main Palace Office|qq=|1=Tonomo-ryЕҚ|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11368767}}, the name of the Saeki faction remains as one of the noble divisions.

Notable figures include {{ill|Saeki Komaro|de|Saeki Komaro|ja|дҪҗдјҜеӯҗйә»е‘Ӯ|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Saeki Komaro|qq=|1=Saeki no Komaro|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11382809}}, who, following {{ill|Prince Nakano-ЕҢe|de|Prinz Nakano-ЕҢe|ja|дёӯеӨ§е…„зҡҮеӯҗ|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Prince Nakano-ЕҢe|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to еӨ©жҷәеӨ©зҡҮ|1=Tenji|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q314802}}, assassinated [[:en:Soga no Iruka|Soga no Iruka]], and {{ill|Saeki Imao Hito|de|Saeki Imao Hito|ja|дҪҗдјҜд»ҠжҜӣдәә|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Saeki Imao Hito|qq=|1=Saeki no Imaemishi|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11382787}}, who was active in government from the Nara to the Heian period and held positions such as [[:en:Sangi (Japan)|Sangi]] and {{ill|Dazai no Mikoto|de|Dazai no Mikoto|ja|еӨӘе®°еёҘ|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Dazai no Mikoto|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to еӨ§е®°еёҘ|1=Dazai-no-sochi|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11434484}}. The clan also produced many warriors, including {{ill|Saeki Tankeide|de|Saeki Tankeide|ja|дҪҗдјҜдё№зөҢжүӢ|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Saeki Tankeide|qq=|1=Saeki no Nifute|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q45828498}} (the father of Komaro), who, following [[:en:Soga no Umako|Soga no Umako]], executed {{ill|Prince Anahobe|de|Prinz Anahobe|ja|з©ҙз©ӮйғЁзҡҮеӯҗ|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Prince Anahobe|qq=}}; {{ill|Saeki Ishiyu|de|Saeki Ishiyu|ja|дҪҗдјҜзҹіж№Ҝ|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Saeki Ishiyu|qq=|1=Saeki no Iwayu|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11382879}}, the Ezo General after the conquest of Echigo; and {{ill|Saeki Katsuragi|de|Saeki Katsuragi|ja|дҪҗдјҜи‘ӣеҹҺ|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Saeki Katsuragi|qq=|1=Saeki no Kazuragi|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11382895}} (the grandson of Ishiyu), the Deputy General of the Eastern Expedition.

Apart from Imao Hito, no one ascended to the position of {{ill|Giseikan|de|Giseikan|ja|иӯ°ж”ҝе®ҳ|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Giseikan|qq=|1=Giseikan|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11632467}} {{sfn|ж—Ҙжң¬еӨ§зҷҫз§‘е…Ёжӣё}}, and the clan eventually declined from being mid-level nobles to lower-Ranked officials ({{ill|Underground Officials|de|Underground Officials|ja|ең°дёӢе®¶|1=Jigeke|2=ja|3=ең°дёӢе®¶|lt=Jigeke|lt=Underground Officials|lt_ja=ең°дёӢе®ҳдәә|lt_de=Underground Officials|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Underground Officials|13=User:Immanuelle/Jigeke|qq=|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11424052}}). Until around the [[:en:Sengoku period|Sengoku Period]], together with the [[:en:ЕҢtomo clan (ancient)|Otomo Clan]], {{ill|Wake Clan|de|Wake Clan|ja|е’Ңж°—ж°Ҹ|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Wake Clan|qq=|1=Wake clan|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11417729}}, and the [[:en:Kudara no Konikishi clan|Baekje Royal Family]], the clan was considered one that received [[:en:Imperial, royal and noble ranks|Noble Titles]] upon the accession of an emperor<ref>{{ill|Tajima no Kimoto|de|Tajima no Kimoto|ja|з”°еі¶е…¬|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tajima no Kimoto|qq=|1=Isao Tajima|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q45819717}} "The Establishment of Noble Titles вҖ“ Rituals, Service, and Conferment" in {{sfn|еҸІжһ—}} 71-1, [[:en:1988|1988 AD]], p. 61</ref>.

Among the lower-Ranked officials bearing the Saeki name, there is the {{ill|Ono Family|de|Ono-Familie|ja|е°ҸйҮҺе®¶ (дҪҗдјҜе§“)|lt=Ono Family|lt_ja=е°ҸйҮҺе®¶|lt_de=Ono-Familie|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ono Family|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}, which produced the materia medica scholar [[:en:Ono Ranzan|Ono Ransan]], and the painter [[:en:Kishi Ganku|Kishi Koma]], who founded the {{ill|Kishi School|de|Kishi-Schule|ja|еІёжҙҫ|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kishi School|qq=|1=Kishi school|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11475951}} and served the [[:en:Arisugawa-no-miya|Arisugawa-no-miya]] family, bearing the Saeki name.

== Related Clans ==
=== Saeki Tsukuri ===
'''Saeki Tsukuri''' (-Miyatsuko) appears in the вҖҳ[[:en:Shinsen ShЕҚjiroku|New Compilation of Surnames]]вҖҷ under the [[:en:Ukyo|Right Capital]] Divine Separation section, and his former name was "Saeki Faction". According to the [[:en:Nihon Shoki|Nihon Shoki]], he was a retainer of [[:en:Ichinobe no Oshiwa|Ichinobe Oshi]] and a descendant of {{ill|Saeki Faction Naka-chiko|de|Saeki Fraktion Naka-chiko|ja|дҪҗдјҜйғЁд»Іеӯҗ|lt=Naka-chiko|lt_ja=гҒӘгҒӢгҒЎгҒ“|lt_de=Naka-chiko|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Saeki Faction Naka-chiko|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to дҪҗдјҜйғЁеЈІијӘ|1=Saekibe no Uruwa|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q85876437}}<ref>In the Pre-accession Annals of [[:en:Emperor YЕ«ryaku|Emperor YЕ«ryaku]], in the 3rd year, October 1 clause of [[:en:Emperor AnkЕҚ|Emperor Ankan]], he is referred to as "Saeki Faction Uruba" (вҖ“uruba), also known as "Naka-teko" (гҒӘгҒӢгҒЎгҒ“).</ref> and, in the 5th year, February 5 clause of [[:en:Emperor Ninken|Emperor Ninken]], he was appointed to oversee the Saeki factions from various provinces.

=== Saeki Obito ===
'''Saeki Obito''' (-Obito) appears in the вҖҳ[[:en:Shinsen ShЕҚjiroku|New Compilation of Surnames]]вҖҷ in [[:en:Kawachi Province|Kawachi Province]] under the {{ill|Divine Separation|de|Divine Separation|ja|зҘһеҲҘ|1=Shinbetsu|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Divine Separation|13=User:Immanuelle/Shinbetsu|qq=}} category.

== Saeki Faction ==
The Saeki Clan oversaw the central [[:en:Saeki people|Saeki Faction]] within the [[:en:Shinabe clans|Official Division]],<ref>{{Cite kotobank|Saeki Clan|encyclopedia=Sekai Dai Hyakka Jiten 2nd edition|accessdate=2021-12-19}}</ref> while the regional Saeki Faction was overseen by {{ill|Saeki Nao|de|Saeki Nao|ja|дҪҗдјҜзӣҙ|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Saeki Nao|qq=|1=Nao Saeki|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11382874}} {{sfn|ж—Ҙжң¬еӨ§зҷҫз§‘е…Ёжӣё}}.

